Gangakhed, Maharashtra, India

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 18.966354, 76.748077.

A small city with the population close to 50,000 people, Gangakhed is situated in central Maharashtra, about 55 miles from the city of Nanded. The city is a historic center and a religious spot, famous as a birthplace of Shree Sant Janabai, a prominent character of MarƒÅthi religious branch. There are a few factories in the town, including a large sugar factory and corn oil producing factory.
